<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-05T06:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-05T06:44:00-05:00" n="539" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d539">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">702.6282/52: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-05T11:00:00-00:44">November
                                    5, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 2:33 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>373. Gottfried von Waldheim German Consul General accompanied by Franz
                            Noelke Vice Consul and Carl Heinzbrand clerk left Monrovia this morning
                            at 11 o’clock by French plane for Abidjan, French Ivory Coast. Tomorrow
                            at 10 o’clock they will leave Abidjan by train for Bobo-Dioulasso, where
                            on November 10 they will take a French commercial plane for Algiers.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hibbard</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>